===United Kingdom===

====Devolved institutions====
* '''[[Northern Ireland Assembly]]:''' "BE IT ENACTED by being passed by the Northern Ireland Assembly and assented to by Her [His] Majesty as follows:"<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.legislation.gov.uk/nia/2008/12/introduction | title=Charities Act (Northern Ireland) 2008 | accessdate=July 22, 2012 | author=[[Northern Ireland Assembly]]}}</ref>
* '''[[Scottish Parliament]]:''' Acts of the Scottish Parliament do not begin with a conventional enacting clause. Instead they begin with a phrase that reads: "The Bill for this Act of the Scottish Parliament was passed by the Parliament on [Date] and received Royal Assent on [Date]"<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.legislation.gov.uk/asp/2005/16/introduction | title=Licensing (Scotland) Act 2005 | date=November 16, 2005 | accessdate=July 22, 2012 | author=[[Scottish Parliament]]}}</ref>
* '''[[National Assembly for Wales]]:'''
:'''Acts in the English Language:''' "Having been passed by the National Assembly for Wales and having received the assent of Her Majesty, it is enacted as follows:—"<ref>{{cite web | url=http://senedd.assemblywales.org/documents/s9073/Local%20Government%20Byelaws%20Wales%20Bill,%20As%20Passed%20unchecked%20version.pdf | title=Local Government Byelaws (Wales) Bill | accessdate=July 22, 2012 | author=[[National Assembly for Wales]] | format=PDF}}</ref>
:'''Acts in the Welsh Language:''' "Gan ei fod wedi ei basio gan Gynulliad Cenedlaethol Cymru a chael cysyniad Ei Mawrhydi, deddfir fel a ganlyn:—"
:'''Measures in the English Language:''' "This Measure, passed by the National Assembly for Wales on [''Date''] and approved by Her Majesty in Council on [''Date''], enacts the following provisions:—"<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.legislation.gov.uk/mwa/2011/7/introduction | title=Education (Wales) Measure 2011 | date=May 10, 2011 | accessdate=July 22, 2012 | author=[[National Assembly for Wales]]}}</ref>
:'''Measures in the Welsh Language:''' "Mae'r Mesur hwn, a basiwyd gan Gynulliad Cenedlaethol Cymru ar [''Dyddiad''] ac a gymeradwywyd gan Ei Mawrhydi yn Ei Chyngor ar [''Dyddiad''], yn deddfu'r darpariaethau a ganlyn:—"

